{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"c378c4c7-89c7-41c8-b4d0-e65c9ec91483","content":"Good news — with .NET 10 SDK, `dotnet test` uses Microsoft.Testing.Platform **by default**. The `TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport` property was the .NET 9 opt-in and is now redundant. You can simply remove it:","toolRequests":[{"toolCallId":"toolu_vrtx_01EQyvz7fycAWAsW4APKSA8r","name":"report_intent","arguments":{"intent":"Removing redundant property"},"type":"function"},{"toolCallId":"toolu_vrtx_01GpahYr5kG1YtKFibZJuBrj","name":"edit","arguments":{"path":"/tmp/sv-27c567a3a8064cecb13615f3f34d4097/TestProject.csproj","old_str":"    <TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>true</TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>\n","new_str":""},"type":"function","intentionSummary":"edit the file at /tmp/sv-27c567a3a8064cecb13615f3f34d4097/TestProject.csproj."}],"interactionId":"93e97b92-63e5-4791-922b-73a0f5b755b7","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is on .NET 10 SDK (10.0.100) and is using MSTest with `EnableMSTestRunner` and `TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport`. \n\nIn .NET 10, `dotnet test` natively uses Microsoft.Testing.Platform (MTP) as the default test runner. The `TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport` property was needed in .NET 9 to opt into MTP support with `dotnet test`, but in .NET 10 it's no longer necessary because MTP is the default.\n\nLet me provide clear guidance:\n\n1. In .NET 10, `dotnet test` uses MTP by default — no need for `TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport`.\n\n\n2. They should remove `TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport` since it's now redundant in .NET 10.\n3. `EnableMSTestRunner` is still required though, as it ensures the test project builds as a self-contained executable that leverages MTP.","outputTokens":491,"requestId":"67D3:226394:2A52548:2EAC49C:69FD3627"},"id":"c62f8fd2-266a-4e7d-83a3-6f8973dcb2eb","timestamp":"2026-05-08T01:02:39.854Z","parentId":"e8f50ec8-9eaa-4fae-8df1-112a3d9194e7"}
